About this item

  • Extend Your 3.5mm Aux Port: Ugreen 3.5mm audio extension cable extends the connection between your iPhone, iPod, MP3 players, smarphones, tablet or any other 3.5mm aux port equipped devices to your headphone, earphone, speaker, car stereo or home theater system etc.
  • Protect Your Aux Port: This extension audio cable is a great solution to protect your 3.5mm aux port from repeat pluging and unpluging. It's costy to buy a new device, while it's so easy to get a 3.5mm auxiliary aux cable.
  • Supported Devices: Auxiliary extension audio cable is compliant with all devices with 3.5mm audio port, like Apple iPhone 6s/6s Plus/6/6 Plus/SE/5s/5c/5/4s/4, iPod, iPad, iPad Pro/Air 2/3/Mini, Samsung Galaxy s2/s3/s4/s5/s6/s6 Edge/s7/s7 Edge, Note 2/3/4/5, Note Edge, HTC M8/M9, Android, Google Nexus smartphones and tablets, Microsoft Surface, portable speakers, headphones, MP3 players, receivers, car stereos and other devices.
  • Material: Pure copper provide maximum's conductivity and durability. Gold plated connectors resist corrosion and ensure optimum sound quality. Tangle-free design makes it easy to use and store. Step-down design makes it possible to work without removing your phone/tablet case.
  • Important Notes: If you use TRRS headphones (4-conductor) with this extension cable, the audio will work but the Mic won't.It also does not work with the inline volume control on the headphone.

Premium 3.5mm Male to Female Audio Extension Cable

  • UGREEN Premium 3.5mm extension cable could extend any 3.5mm auxiliary jack up to the longer length. It brings your favorite music by connecting your mobile devices, like an iPhone, iPod or any MP3 player to a car stereo or speaker system.
  • Perfect quality let you enjoy a wonderful life. The slim metal case connector allows you to plug it to your source device without taking off your mobile/Tab case.

Stereo Sound Quality

Dual-shielding, high purity copper material, and durable Golden-plated connectors. Seamlessly transmits stereo audio for high-quality sound, while ensuring reliability and lossless audio transmission.

Installation

Plug & Play: Ready to use, once each end is connected to its respective port on a compatible device.

Important Note

This 3.5mm male to female audio cable Does Not support Microphone.

Specification

Premium quality metal connectors: straight head Stereo Jack 3.5 mm male to female.

24K Gold plated plugs for optimum sound quality.

Pure copper provides maximum's conductivity and durability.

Connect your Cell Phone, iPod, MP3 player, Tablet or PC to your home audio system.

Package Content

UGREEN 3.5mm Male to female extension Stereo Cable x1

Polished metal connectors ensures no audio signal loss.

Premium PVC jacket and round design make the cable more flexible and tangle-free.

The slim connector makes it fit phones easily with a thicker case.

      Squeef
      4.0 out of 5 stars Excellent cable, questionable QA
      Reviewed in the United States on December 28, 2015
      Size: 6FTVerified Purchase
      Product looks much better in person than it does in photos. The metal sleeves on the plugs have a really nice finish on them, and the light plays exceptionally well off the surface. Unfortunately, when I tried to plug them in the first time, the sleeve immediately slipped off. It looked like there was only small dab of glue holding the sleeve onto the connector. I applied some loctite adhesive onto the sleeve, and it seems to be holding up well.

      One really nice thing that I like about this cable is that the connector end is very skinny and long. One of my phone cases is quite thick, and another cable that I have wouldn't actually fit, despite having a step down design. This cable should be able to reach the headphone jack on a phone even if the case is exceptionally thick.

      Ugreen should definitely have some basic QA for their products. If they just pulled a bit on the sleeve of each connector, they'd be able to catch these defects before they are packaged and shipped out. Not everyone has the proper glue to fix these things.

      Timbo Slims
      4.0 out of 5 stars This cable is OK, but for about the same price I like the Kabeldirekt offering better.
      Reviewed in the United States on June 22, 2017
      Size: 10FTVerified Purchase
      I have tried many 3.5mm extension cables - and lately have compared offerings from Monoprice, Kabeldirekt and Ugreen side by side. The Monoprice cables are the cheapest, and the Ugreen and Kabeldirekt cables sell for about the same price, with the Kabeldirekt averaging about $1 more for the same length cable.

      These Ugreen cables are good - but I rated them four stars because the Kabeldirekt cables are just better. The Ugreen connectors are OK, but the way they are joined to the cable is not as good as the Kabeldirekt version - the connectors on the Kabeldirekt, and how they are joined to the cable, are just sturdier, and made to last. Also, the Kabeldirket cable itself is thicker and more robust than the Ugreen - which when using lengths like 10 or 15 feet for a Headphone extension is important. With longer runs of cable, thicker, more robust cables are a better choice - they don't tangle as easily are are less apt to kink or get damaged when accidentally stepped on.

      As far as comparison of the Ugrenn and Kabeldirekt to the Monoprice, personally I would not go for the Monoprice unless price is the determining factor.

      Overall, the Ugreen is a good, serviceable cable that you would probably be 100% satisfied with, especially in the shorter lengths. I only knocked off a star because, for about the same money, the Kabeldirekt is just a better cable for my needs --- especially for longer length runs due to the extra thickness.

      Thanks for reading.
